Am I the only one who thinks the “shadow” could be representing the negative side of the BTS fandom? I mean the very obsessive, scary fans, who’re willing to do justa bout anything to anyone in the name of the Band or Bias .
The shadow came off as very aggressive in his assurance that there’s no escape and separation from it - it will be there, if he wants it to or not.

I can imagine it to be very scary when you reach a certain level of fame and people start thinking they own you because they love you.

It’s just something that came to mind the first time I watched this. It’s by no means a happy song. It seems more like a cry for help.

snippet.textDisplay: Living in the public eye can lead the celebrities to have lack of confidence, emotional instability, obsessive behavior and inability to adapt. They can feel a sense of deprivation because they don't have enough time with their family and friends. The obsession to succeed and survive in extreme competition can also lead to an inferiority complex. (Dr. Jung Hae-myoung, Korea Times). Let's hope that Suga will be okay. I want him to be happy, whole and safe. I don't know what to make of this song yet. But let's keep supporting him. And hopefully we can eventually hear directly from him what he is conveying in this song. I want a sense of relief that he is doing well. He is such a talented person!!!
